  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting People with Down Syndrome in Africa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Many people with Down syndrome in Africa face low life expectancy, abuse, stigma, segregation and limited life opportunities, both as children and adults. Society&apos;s negative attitudes prevents them from reaching their potential, living valued lives and contributing to society.     This project will provide capacity building training for small Down syndrome charities in Africa, putting them on a sound footing with tools to improve knowledge, attitudes and empower people with Down syndrome.</narrative>
  </description>
